  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic movies?",
  "response": "There are many romantic movies that have captured the hearts of audiences over the years. Here\u2019s a list of some widely regarded romantic films across various eras and styles:\n\n1. **Casablanca** (1942) - A classic love story set during World War II.\n2. **The Notebook** (2004) - A tale of enduring love based on Nicholas Sparks' novel.\n3. **Pride and Prejudice** (2005) - A cinematic adaptation of Jane Austen's beloved novel about love and societal expectations.\n4. **Titanic** (1997) - A passionate romance set against the backdrop of the tragic sinking of the Titanic.\n5. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind** (2004) - A unique take on love and memory, blending romance with science fiction.\n6. **When Harry Met Sally...** (1989) - A romantic comedy exploring the complexities of friendships and relationships.\n7. **La La Land** (2016) - A modern musical that beautifully captures love and ambition in Los Angeles.\n8. **Before Sunrise** (1995) - A romantic drama that explores a deep connection formed between two strangers over one night in Vienna.\n9. **A Walk to Remember** (2002) - Another adaptation of a Nicholas Sparks novel, centered around young love and personal growth.\n10. **Notting Hill** (1999) - A charming romantic comedy about a chance encounter between a bookstore owner and a famous actress.\n\nThese films vary in tone and style, from dramas to comedies to musicals, but they all explore the theme of love in unique ways.",
